&#8220;Yesterday at seven in the evening in a car park in Chamberi (a central district of Madrid) he was in his car and an individual on a motorbike pointed a gun at him and stole his watch,&#8221; the police source told AFP. The Spanish international reported the robbery with an investigation now underway. Widespread reports in the Spanish media valued the watch at 70,000 euros. Koke has still been included in the Atletico squad for Saturday&#8217;s Madrid derby against Real Madrid.